# Builder.io Agent Rules

## Component Reuse Policy

### CRITICAL: Always Use Existing Components First:

- `client/components/ui/` - These are the reusable components that must be used when creating components.
- `client/components/` - These are custom components and should be used if a component in `client/components/ui/` is not suitable.
- Check `guidelines/` folder for component documentation
- Only create new components if one is not available in `client/components/ui/` or `client/components/`

## Consult design system documentation

- `guidelines/Button.md`
- `guidelines/` folder for all component specs
- Reference implementations in `client/components/ButtonExample.tsx`

### Specific Component Rules

#### Buttons

- **ALWAYS use**: `client/components/ui/Button.tsx` (uppercase B)
- **NEVER create**: Custom button elements with inline styles or hard-coded colors
- **MUST use LD 3.5 tokens**: Button component internally uses all LD semantic tokens
- **Variants**: `primary`, `secondary`, `tertiary`, `destructive`
- **Sizes**: `small`, `medium`, `large`
- **Import**: `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button'`

**Token Usage** (Button component uses these internally - DO NOT override):

- Colors: `var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary)`, `var(--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-secondary)`, etc.
- Typography: `var(--ld-semantic-font-family-sans)`
- Focus: `var(--ld-semantic-color-action-focus-outline)`
- Border radius: `9999px` (pill-shaped, per LD 3.5 spec)

#### Button Groups

- **ALWAYS use**: `client/components/ui/ButtonGroup.tsx`
- **Never use**: Manual flex containers for buttons
- **Import**: `import { ButtonGroup } from '@/components/ui/ButtonGroup'`

#### Tags & Badges

- **For OLQ scores**: Use `client/components/ui/olq-tag.tsx` (OLQTag component)
- **For general tags**: Use `client/components/ui/tag.tsx` (Tag component)
- **Never use**: Badge component or custom styled spans for tags

#### Popovers & Overlays

- **Use**: `client/components/ui/Popover.tsx` (existing in-repo component)
- **Include arrow**: Import and use `PopoverArrow` component
- **Import**: `import { Popover, PopoverTrigger, PopoverContent, PopoverArrow } from '@/components/ui/Popover'`
- **NEVER**: Install or import from `@radix-ui/*`, `shadcn`, or any external overlay library

### Component Import Paths

**Living Design 3.5 Components (Uppercase)**:

```tsx
import { Button, buttonVariants } from '@/components/ui/Button';
import { ButtonGroup } from '@/components/ui/ButtonGroup';
import { Tag } from '@/components/ui/tag';
import { OLQTag } from '@/components/ui/olq-tag';
```

**All components must be imported from @/components/ui/** — never from external packages:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — always from local repo
import { Popover, PopoverTrigger, PopoverContent } from '@/components/ui/Popover';
import { Dialog, DialogTrigger, DialogContent } from '@/components/ui/Dialog';
import { Select, SelectItem } from '@/components/ui/Select';

// ❌ WRONG — never import UI primitives from external libraries
import { Popover } from '@radix-ui/react-popover';
import { Dialog } from '@radix-ui/react-dialog';
import { Button } from 'shadcn/ui';
```

### Living Design 3.5 Token Usage

**CRITICAL**: All components MUST use LD semantic tokens. NEVER use hard-coded colors or values.

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary` | #0071DC | Primary button background |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary-hovered` | #0060B8 | Primary button hover |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary-pressed` | #004C94 | Primary button active |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-secondary` | #FFFFFF | Secondary button background |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-border-secondary` | #74767C | Secondary button border |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-destructive` | #ea1100 | Destructive button background |
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-focus-outline` | #0071DC | Focus indicator |
| `--ld-semantic-font-family-sans` | Everyday Sans UI | All buttons |
| `--ld-semantic-spacing-3` | 12px | Button group gap |

### Summary — Golden Rules

1. 🔍 Search FIRST, create LAST
2. 📚 Use LD 3.5 components when available
3. 🎨 Always use semantic design tokens
4. 🔄 Consolidate duplicates immediately
5. 📖 Document new components thoroughly
6. ✅ Import Button from uppercase path: `'@/components/ui/Button'`
7. 🚫 NEVER create custom buttons with inline styles
8. 🎯 One canonical component per UI pattern

## Living Design 3.5 Component Inventory

### Buttons & Actions
- ✅ `Button.tsx` - All button needs (primary, secondary, tertiary, destructive)
- ✅ `ButtonGroup.tsx` - Multiple buttons layout
- ✅ `IconButton.tsx` - Icon-only buttons

### Data Display
- ✅ `tag.tsx` - Status tags and labels
- ✅ `olq-tag.tsx` - OLQ percentage badges
- ✅ `badge.tsx` - Notification badges

### Overlays
- ✅ `Popover.tsx` - Popovers with arrow support
- ✅ `Dialog.tsx` - Modal dialogs
- ✅ `AlertDialog.tsx` - Confirmation dialogs

### Forms
- ✅ `Select.tsx` - Dropdown selects
- ✅ `Input.tsx` - Text inputs
- ✅ `Checkbox.tsx` - Checkboxes
- ✅ `Calendar.tsx` - Date picker

### Navigation
- ✅ `Menu.tsx` - Dropdown menus

### Panels & Drawers
- ✅ ALL panels MUST be resizable — See `guidelines/Panel.md`
- REQUIRED: Min width 420px, Max width 800px
- REQUIRED: Resize handle on left edge with visual indicator
- REQUIRED: localStorage persistence of user's preferred width
- REQUIRED: Responsive behavior for small screens
- Reference Implementation: `client/components/RecommendationsPanel.tsx`

## Page Templates & Layout Components (HARD RULE)

### CRITICAL: Always Use Page Template Components

Every page MUST be wrapped in the appropriate page template. Never build bare pages without the standard layout shell.

#### Top Navigation
- **ALWAYS use**: The existing top nav component from `client/components/`
- **NEVER create**: Custom headers, nav bars, or top-level navigation from scratch
- The top nav must appear on every page — no exceptions
- Do not hide, override, or conditionally remove the top nav unless explicitly instructed

#### Bottom Navigation
- **ALWAYS use**: The existing bottom nav component from `client/components/`
- **NEVER create**: Custom footers or bottom bars from scratch
- The bottom nav must appear on every page — no exceptions
- Do not hide, override, or conditionally remove the bottom nav unless explicitly instructed

#### Page Template Shell
- Before building a new page, check `client/components/` for an existing page layout or template wrapper (e.g., `PageLayout`, `ComponentPageLayout`, etc.)
- All new pages MUST use the appropriate layout wrapper — never render content directly without a layout shell
- If a layout wrapper does not exist for the use case, create one that includes the top nav, bottom nav, and a content slot — do not skip the nav components

#### Summary — Page Template Golden Rules

1. Every page = Top Nav + Content + Bottom Nav
2. Search `client/components/` for existing layout wrappers before creating a new page
3. Never conditionally hide nav components without explicit instruction
4. New layout wrappers must always include top and bottom nav
5. Page content must be scoped inside the template's content slot — not alongside nav components

---

## External Library Policy (HARD RULE)

**NEVER install or import from external UI libraries** including:

- `shadcn/ui`
- `@radix-ui/*`
- `@headlessui/*`
- `@mui/*` (Material UI)
- `antd` (Ant Design)
- `chakra-ui`
- Any other third-party component library

All UI components MUST come from `client/components/ui/`. If a needed component doesn't exist there, build it using LD 3.5 design tokens — do not reach for an external package.

---

Remember: **Reuse > Adapt > Create** (in that order!) — always from `client/components/ui/`
